  Linux box, 2 nic's.. iptables.  Its very powerful, lets you do cool stuff like IPsec tunneling in to your office, etc..etc..  It also lets you do verbose logging of attempted portscans, attacks, etc..  You can run snort or other network IDS systems on it, and you can do cool stuff like automatically reject/drop packets from a host who is apparently attacking you, dynamically.  For about $300.00 you can build a headless linux box (cpu, memory, disk, case, floppy drive, and two el-cheapo linksys network cards).  I use an old celeron 300A for mine, but I used to use a Sparc IPX (about like a P66).  Dont need much memory either.   My IPX had 32M and that was overkill.  My current firewall has about 256M of ram in it, but that is just because I *had* it laying around.  Other cool things that I do are SNMP traffic statistic gathering, transparent proxy/cache (squid), and tcpdump for network problem analysis.  FUN STUFF, and it beats the fuck outa using some hardware ''router''.<br>
